FRANK HULSEMAN v. STATE OF MARYLAND. [No. 27,

October Term, 1931.]

Decided December 16th, 1931. *698Harry O. Levin and George Eckhardt, Jr., submitting on brief, for tbe appellant. G. G. A. Anderson, Assistant Attorney General, with whom were Wm. Preston Lane, Jr., Attorney General, Herbert B. O1 Conor, State’s Attorney for Baltimore City, and William H. Maynard, Assistant Slate’s Attorney, on the brief, for tbe State.

Tbe opinion was delivered

per Curiam.
